	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99697309565108><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99697309565108>RE: quers</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99697309565108#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=82076><span id= >serotonin</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 4th 8:58 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I don't know if I should touch this post or not. It is a bit dated...but I will add my two cents..(copper?) I think we're all taking this too personally. It has nothing to do with who got their ass kicked in school, or who has the better class, or whos a higher level than whoever else. Some of you people treat this situation just like every redneck I went to school with...thinking that by saying, "duel me" and fighting it out will solve anything. It's a funny case of EQ Rage. Seriously...you gain little from pounding another PC because he likes his class more than yours. Big deal...so you're a rogue and you wanna pound a bard because for whatever reason you've found something not to like...Does this happen among other classes? How much would a rogue appreciate a Minstrel wanting to pound him/her just because!? It's silly trivial things that tend to become the most annoying things. Lets just realize we've got more in common than alot of other classes. We're in the same boat by many standards, so lets just group together, join forces and wail on all the other classes! :)<br>Much Love and Fond Memories<br>&nbsp;<br>~Serotonin~<br>Punk Rock Diva of the 27th Song</td></tr>
