	   <tr><td colspan=2>The thing about bards are they're the jack-of-all-trades, master of none. Something like Shamans (no offense).Bards are 100% group-oriented one way or another. They're singing is what makes them shine. Singing and instrument playing makes them the master of this one skill, and that's all. There are 3 races to pick and they vary greatly. The major stats I believe are Charisma (buying and selling to vendors), a little bit of Stamina and Strength, and maybe some dexterity or agility. Bards can tank, but not albeit as well as warriors. They can sing to do damange, but they're not as efficient or powerful like true casters. Bards are a hybrid class, thus making experience gaining very slow for them unlike others. The only major weakness I can find is that if you want to use your trading skills, they may be weak due to your character choice (Half-elves: 60 wisdom, 75 intelligenc, not a good market race, at the beginning.....<br>One last note: People are saying bards are the fasteset class. Partially TRUE! There aren't a lot of characters and npcs that can be faster than a drum-wielding bard using his speed songs to glide, but their are.<br>And a final tip/trick: Try using an instrument (like a drum for speed). Thus you can run fast and if you're attack, just keep using it until you're a distance away and THEN! you can decide if you want to attack it or not. (Easier than having a weapon, then you want to run, replacing the weapon with the drum or whatever; all the while taking damage)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
