	   <tr><td colspan=2>The thing about bards are they're the jack-of-all-trades, master of none. Something like Shamans (no offense).Bards are 100% group-oriented one way or another. They're singing is what makes them shine. Singing and instrument playing makes them the master of this one skill, and that's all. There are 3 races to pick and they vary greatly. The major stats I believe are Charisma (buying and selling to vendors), a little bit of Stamina and Strength, and maybe some dexterity or agility. Bards can tank, but not albeit as well as warriors. They can sing to do damange, but they're not as efficient or powerful like true casters. Bards are a hybrid class, thus making experience gaining very slow for them unlike others. The only major weakness I can find is that if you want to use your trading skills, they may be weak due to your character choice (Half-elves: 60 wisdom, 75 intelligenc, not a good market race, at the beginning.....<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
